{
  "title": "Building Microsoft Q&A Assist: An Advanced RAG",
  "authors": ["Tom FitzMacken", "Joel Martinez", "Jeremy Stayton"],
  "abstract": "This article describes the development of Microsoft Q&A Assist, an advanced RAG-based chat system that uses a service-oriented architecture to provide high-quality answers to user questions. The system was built by Skilling engineers over several months and required solving various technical, product, and organizational challenges.",
  "keywords": ["RAG", "chat system", "service-oriented architecture", "Microsoft Q&A Assist"],
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "The article begins with an introduction to the concept of RAG-based chat systems and their limitations. It then describes the goals and objectives of the Microsoft Q&A Assist project."
    },
    {
      "title": "Building the Golden Dataset",
      "text": "The authors describe the importance of building a golden dataset, which is a carefully curated and annotated dataset that serves as a benchmark for evaluating the performance of AI models. They explain how this dataset was built by working with experts across various technologies."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solving the Challenge of Non-Determinism",
      "text": "The authors discuss the challenge of non-determinism in generative AI systems and how it can be addressed by developing a golden dataset. They explain how this dataset was used to evaluate the performance of the system."
    },
    {
      "title": "Trailblazing with Q&A Assist",
      "text": "The authors describe the challenges faced by the Skilling engineers while building Q&A Assist, including solving new technical, product, and organizational challenges. They explain how the team had to become a forcing function to drive answers to questions they needed to move forward."
    },
    {
      "title": "A Milestone and an Opportunity",
      "text": "The authors describe the introduction of Microsoft Q&A Assist in May 2023 as a significant milestone in harnessing Microsoft Learn content in a new way for customers. They explain how the team collaborated with the Azure Portal team to expose the underlying RAG system as a web API."
    },
    {
      "title": "Ask Learn: An Expanded Role",
      "text": "The authors describe the expanded role of Ask Learn, which is now used by Microsoft Copilot for Azure. They explain how the results from Ask Learn are used in several ways, including providing end users with a way to access information while working in the Azure portal."
    }
  ]
}

