{
  "title": "Improving Search Relevance on DoorDash",
  "text": "We redesigned the search pipeline to improve recall and precision. We built a three-part pipeline that identifies, interprets, and elaborates upon any query within the base set. The new ranking model uses a pointwise learn-to-rank mechanism by including search context information.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Rethinking the Search Flow",
      "text": "Our analysis revealed opportunities for improvement on both the precision and the ranking fronts. We didn't have a sophisticated ranking model to incorporate information from the search context beyond lexical similarities between query and search entities."
    },
    {
      "title": "Building a Base Dataset",
      "text": "We focused our improvements on DoorDash's 100 most popular queries from the previous month. This set accounts for a substantial percentage, greater than 20%, of our overall query volume."
    },
    {
      "title": "Rethinking Our Fixes",
      "text": "For the first iteration, we created the simplest possible search pipeline that could help fix our recall and precision problems. We made changes in the two steps of our search pipeline: on the recall front and on the precision front."
    },
    {
      "title": "Redesigning the Recall Step",
      "text": "Our design of the new recall pipeline had two main goals: make search results more relevant for our consumers and make our search results more intuitive. We constructed a three-part pipeline to accomplish these goals."
    },
    {
      "title": "Standardizing Queries",
      "text": "We noticed that consumers often do not mention a concept in the base set directly, but refer to it using a colloquial synonym. To ensure that these minor differences do not distort our pipeline's understanding of the underlying concept, we removed noise from each query and converted them into a canonical or standardized form."
    },
    {
      "title": "Query Understanding with Concept Identification and Entity Linking",
      "text": "Given the canonical form of the query, we want to use entity-linking to identify the concept in the base set mentioned by the user and create a knowledge graph traversal to derive similar concepts to the one being queried."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "title": "A System for Balancing Supply and Demand",
  "abstract": "This system uses machine learning (ML) algorithms to forecast supply and demand, and then allocates incentives to balance the two.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "The system is designed to balance supply and demand in a dynamic environment. It uses ML algorithms to forecast supply and demand, and then allocates incentives to balance the two."
    },
    {
      "title": "Forecasting with ML",
      "text": "The system uses LightGBM framework for forecasting. It has several advantages over other frameworks, including support for multivariate forecasting, extrapolation, and counterfactuals."
    },
    {
      "title": "Choosing an Optimizer",
      "text": "The system uses a mixed-integer programming (MIP) approach to optimize incentive allocation. The optimizer has a custom objective function of minimizing undersupply with several constraints."
    },
    {
      "title": "Dealing with Uncertainty",
      "text": "The system generates expected estimates of hours gap from forecasts using a resampling process. This helps to address the issue of variance and over-allocate incentives to places that exhibit high variance relative to places that have low variance."
    }
  ]
}

