{
  "title": "Building a Unified User Foundation Model for Grab's Superapp Ecosystem",
  "authors": [
    {
      "name": "Grab Authors"
    }
  ],
  "abstract": "This paper presents a unified user foundation model designed to capture the complex and diverse interactions between users, merchants, and drivers across all verticals of Grab's superapp ecosystem. The model is built on a transformer architecture that jointly pre-trains on tabular and time-series data with different modalities. It tackles four fundamental challenges: jointly training on tabular and time-series data, handling a wide variety of data modalities, generalising beyond a single task, and scaling to massive entity vocabularies.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "Grab's superapp ecosystem is a complex system that requires a unified user foundation model to capture the diverse interactions between users, merchants, and drivers across all verticals."
    },
    {
      "title": "Challenges and Opportunities of Diverse Modalities",
      "text": "The sheer variety of data modalities presents several significant challenges and opportunities for building a unified user foundation model. Data heterogeneity is a major challenge, as different data types do not naturally lend themselves to being combined."
    },
    {
      "title": "Model Architecture",
      "text": "Grab's transformer architecture enables joint pre-training on tabular and time-series data with different modalities. It tackles four fundamental challenges: jointly training on tabular and time-series data, handling a wide variety of data modalities, generalising beyond a single task, and scaling to massive entity vocabularies."
    },
    {
      "title": "Unifying Tabular and Time-Series Data",
      "text": "A key architectural challenge lies in jointly training on both tabular and time-series data. Our solution begins with a novel tokenisation strategy that defines a universal token structure as a key:value pair."
    },
    {
      "title": "Handling Diverse Modalities with an Adapter-Based Design",
      "text": "The model uses a flexible adapter-based design to manage the diversity of data modalities. Each adapter acts as a specialised \"expert\" encoder for a specific modality, transforming its unique data format into a unified, high-dimensional vector space."
    },
    {
      "title": "Unsupervised Pre-Training for a Complex Ecosystem",
      "text": "A powerful model architecture is only half the story; the learning strategy determines the quality and generality of the knowledge captured in the final embeddings. Our goal is to capture the complex and diverse interactions between our users, merchants, and drivers across all verticals."
    },
    {
      "title": "Conclusion",
      "text": "This paper presents a unified user foundation model designed to capture the complex and diverse interactions between users, merchants, and drivers across all verticals of Grab's superapp ecosystem. The model is built on a transformer architecture that jointly pre-trains on tabular and time-series data with different modalities."
    }
  ]
}

