{
  "title": "Woowa Brothers' AI Data Analyst: QueryAnswerBird (QAB)",
  "description": "A comprehensive overview of QAB's architecture, development process, and features.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Architecture",
      "content": "QAB's architecture is composed of four main components: (1) Unstructured data pipeline based on vector store, (2) RAG-based multi-chain structure for various literacy features, (3) LLMOps for development, deployment, and operation of LLM service, and (4) Implementation of various response features based on Slack."
    },
    {
      "title": "Development Process",
      "content": "The development process involved short sprints with task force teams working together to achieve goals within limited resources. Team members rotated tasks for each sprint to understand each other's strengths and interests, leading to stronger teamwork and motivation."
    },
    {
      "title": "Text-to-SQL Feature",
      "content": "QAB's Text-to-SQL feature was developed using a new structure focusing on four elements: data augmentation, development of search algorithm, prompt engineering, and establishment of system for testing and evaluation. The feature uses DocumentLoader, Vectorstore, and RAG QA provided by LangChain to generate LLM responses based on domain knowledge."
    },
    {
      "title": "Character Design",
      "content": "The character design of QAB was created with the help of Woowa Brothers' Design Group. The character has a cute nerdy image, combining a computer folder with a pelican, and is composed of complex systems on the inside."
    }
  ]
}

