{
  "title": "Hybrid Search: Combining Keyword Matching and Vector Search for Enhanced Recall and Relevance",
  "authors": ["Ines Soveral"],
  "date": "2023-02-20T00:00:00.000Z",
  "abstract": "This article discusses the implementation of Hybrid Search, a combination of keyword matching and vector search, to enhance recall and relevance in the OLX marketplace.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "The OLX marketplace uses a traditional keyword-based retrieval system, which can lead to limitations in recall and relevance. To address this issue, we implemented Hybrid Search, combining keyword matching with vector search."
    },
    {
      "title": "Vector Search Implementation",
      "text": "We used the E5-small variant of the pre-trained embedding model for semantic search tasks. This model is optimized for lightweight inference and supports inputs up to 512 tokens, enabling us to embed both ad titles and descriptions."
    },
    {
      "title": "Combining Retrieval Sets",
      "text": "To combine keyword matching and vector search results, we used a fixed-size allocation approach. A set number of results would be retrieved via vector search, with the remainder filled by keyword matches."
    },
    {
      "title": "Learning to Rank (LTR) Model",
      "text": "Our LTR model is based on XGBoost and uses a range of features derived from historical user behavior, ad characteristics, and keyword-based BM25 scores. We retrained the LTR model to incorporate vector-specific features."
    },
    {
      "title": "Initial Experimentation and Results",
      "text": "We conducted an experiment with vector search in the search extensions space, which showed a more than 100% increase in successful events per user. This confirmed our hypothesis: vector search can meaningfully enhance recall and relevance."
    },
    {
      "title": "Hybrid Search Enablement",
      "text": "We implemented Hybrid Search in the main flow by integrating vector search with the keyword-based retrieval set and re-ranking the combined results using our LTR model. We used a linear re-ranking strategy to temporarily replace LTR, which allowed us to collect data for future model training."
    },
    {
      "title": "Hybrid Search in the Main Flow",
      "text": "We launched an A/B/C test structure to assess how Hybrid Search performs with both ranking models. Unfortunately, the test did not reach convergence due to traffic being split across three variants. We re-launched the experiment, focusing solely on the Vanilla LTR variant."
    },
    {
      "title": "Conclusion",
      "text": "Hybrid Search has shown promising results in enhancing recall and relevance in the OLX marketplace. We plan to roll out Hybrid Search across all markets, starting with our largest, and continue to iterate by fine-tuning embedding models and refining the solution."
    }
  ]
}

