{
  "title": "Vespa Implementation",
  "description": "Implementation details for Vespa project",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Introduction",
      "content": "This document outlines the implementation details of the Vespa project."
    },
    {
      "name": "Consistency Requirements",
      "content": "The key requirement was to integrate the dense retrieval into the existing setup. This means:\n\n* Support a hard limit on the number of dense retrieval matches added to the Top-K results as simply flooding results with approximate matches is a bad user experience.\n\n* Adding a filter should not increase the number of search results.\n\n* Avoid surprise when changing the sorting of search results."
    },
    {
      "name": "Approach",
      "content": "There were only a few paths to go:\n\n* Ignore the problem (not an option)\n\n* Two requests to Vespa and combine the results in the application layer (unattractive)\n\n* Push the complexity down to Vespa (chosen approach)"
    },
    {
      "name": "Reciprocal Rank Fusion",
      "content": "A.k.a. RRF is a Vespa ranking feature available in the global-phase. It is defined as rrf_score = 1.0 / (k + rank). The score depends on an arbitrary parameter k and the rank (position) within a virtual list of search results ranked by some ranking feature, e.g. nearest neighbor similarity."
    },
    {
      "name": "Identifying Nearest Neighbor Matches",
      "content": "All documents matched by the nearestNeighbor query clause has a non 0 itemRawScore rank feature. However, to answer if the document is matched only by the nearestNeighbor the we need to know if the document was not matched by other query clauses."
    },
    {
      "name": "Using Global Ranking Phase as Filter",
      "content": "Matches from all content nodes are available in the container node in the global ranking phase. It supports a rank-score-drop-limit parameter that can be used to remove matched documents whose score is lower than some constant numeric value."
    },
    {
      "name": "Putting All Together",
      "content": "Here is the implementation that limits the nearest neighbor matches count using the tricks described above:"
    }
  ]
}

