{
  "title": "Enhanced Agentic RAG for On-Call Copilot Genie",
  "authors": ["Uber Engineering"],
  "abstract": "This paper presents an enhanced agentic RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) framework, EAg-RAG, designed to improve the accuracy and relevancy of on-call copilot Genie's answers in the engineering security and privacy domain. The framework introduces LLM-powered agents for pre-retrieval and post-processing steps, enhancing context relevance and extracted content before answer generation.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "The on-call copilot Genie is a critical tool for Uber's engineering security and privacy teams. However, its accuracy and relevancy were limited by traditional RAG approaches."
    },
    {
      "title": "Challenges",
      "text": "Two key challenges hindered the development of an accurate and reliable on-call copilot: high SME involvement and slow evaluation, and marginal gains and plateauing accuracy."
    },
    {
      "title": "Agentic RAG Answer Generation",
      "text": "The EAg-RAG framework introduces LLM-powered agents in pre-retrieval and post-processing steps to improve context relevance and extracted content before answer generation. The Query Optimizer refines the query when it lacks context or is ambiguous, while the Source Identifier processes the optimized query to narrow down the subset of policy documents most likely to contain relevant answers."
    },
    {
      "title": "Challenges",
      "text": "The EAg-RAG framework addresses the challenges faced in developing an accurate and reliable on-call copilot. Automated evaluation with generative AI and the agentic RAG framework reduces experiment evaluation time from weeks to minutes, enabling faster iterations and more effective directional experimentation."
    },
    {
      "title": "Use Cases at Uber",
      "text": "The EAg-RAG framework was tested for the on-call copilot Genie within the engineering security and privacy domain. In these domains, it showed a significant improvement in the accuracy and relevancy of the golden test-set answers."
    }
  ]
}

