{
"article": {
"title": "GenAI-Powered Invoice Automation System at Uber",
"authors": ["Uber"],
"datePublished": "2023-02-20T00:00:00.000Z",
"dateModified": "2023-03-01T00:00:00.000Z"
},
"abstract": {
"text": "This article describes the design and implementation of a GenAI-powered invoice automation system at Uber, which has achieved remarkable results in reducing manual processing, improving accuracy, and enhancing user experience."
},
"sections": [
{
"title": "Introduction",
"text": "The article begins by introducing the problem of manual invoicing and its associated challenges. It highlights the need for an automated solution that can accurately extract data from invoices and reduce manual processing time."
},
{
"title": "Design Principles",
"text": "The design principles of the GenAI-powered invoice automation system are discussed, including accuracy, scalability, flexibility, and user experience. The article explains how these principles guided the development of the system."
},
{
"title": "Architecture",
"text": "The architecture of the system is described in detail, including the use of TextSense as a document processing platform. The article explains how the system integrates with existing systems and processes invoices from various sources."
},
{
"title": "Model Evaluation and Selection",
"text": "The process of evaluating and selecting models for the GenAI-powered invoice automation system is discussed. The article highlights the importance of data preparation, model fine-tuning, and evaluation metrics in achieving high accuracy."
},
{
"title": "Results",
"text": "The results of implementing the GenAI-powered invoice automation system at Uber are presented, including a significant reduction in manual processing time, high accuracy rates, and improved user experience."
}
],
"keywords": [
"Invoice Automation",
"GenAI",
"TextSense",
"Document Processing Platform"
]
}

{
  "title": "Personalized Content Optimization for Uber CRM",
  "abstract": "This paper presents a personalized content optimization framework for Uber's Customer Relationship Management (CRM) system. The framework leverages machine learning models and contextual bandit algorithms to optimize the open rates of email communications sent to end-users.",
  "keywords": [
    "personalization",
    "content optimization",
    "machine learning",
    "contextual bandits",
    "email marketing"
  ],
  "authors": [
    {
      "name": "John Doe",
      "affiliation": "Uber Inc."
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "text": "The paper introduces the problem of optimizing email open rates for Uber's CRM system. It highlights the importance of personalization in improving user engagement and satisfaction."
    },
    {
      "title": "Methodology",
      "text": "The framework uses a combination of machine learning models (XGBoost, LinUCB) and contextual bandit algorithms (SquareCB) to optimize email open rates. The models are trained on historical data from Uber's CRM system and user feedback."
    },
    {
      "title": "Results",
      "text": "The results show that the framework significantly improves email open rates compared to traditional methods. The paper also discusses the limitations of the current approach and potential areas for future research."
    }
  ],
